    • Nurse

      public Nurse(String firstName, String surname, String phoneNumber, String status, LocalDate deletionDate, LocalDate archiveDate, String changedBy, String deletedBy)
      Constructor to initiate an object of class Nurse with the given parameter. Use this constructor to initiate objects, which are not persisted yet, because it will not have a nurse id (nid).
      Parameter:
      firstName - First name of the nurse.
      surname - Last name of the nurse.
      phoneNumber - phone Number of the nurse.

    • Nurse

      public Nurse(long nid, String firstName, String surname, String phoneNumber, String status, LocalDate deletionDate, LocalDate archiveDate, String changedBy, String deletedBy)
      Constructor to initiate an object of class Nurse with the given parameter. Use this constructor to initiate objects, which are already persisted and have a nurse id (nid).
      Parameter:
      nid - nurse id.
      firstName - First name of the nurse.
      surname - Last name of the nurse.
      phoneNumber - phoneNumber of the nurse

    • markForDeletion

      public void markForDeletion()
      Marks the nurse for future deletion by setting the archive date to the current date and the deletion date to 10 years from now. Optionally sets the status to inactive. This method is typically used for soft-deletion workflows.
